SIMPLE: tetrapneumona
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tetrapneumona
<hw>Tet`rap*neu"mo*na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Tetra-</er>, and <er>Pneumo-</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A division of Arachnida including those spiders which have four
lungs, or pulmonary sacs. It includes the bird spiders
(<gen>Mygale</gen>) and the trapdoor spiders. See
<er>Mygale</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tetrapnuemonian</ent>⟦br⟧
